SELECT study_name, COUNT(data_id) AS num_data_points FROM ProteinExpressionStudies LEFT JOIN ProteinExpressionData ON ProteinExpressionStudies.study_id = ProteinExpressionData.study_id GROUP BY study_name;

SELECT study_name, protein_name, expression_value FROM ProteinExpressionStudies JOIN ProteinExpressionData ON ProteinExpressionStudies.study_id = ProteinExpressionData.study_id WHERE expression_value > 10;

SELECT study_name, target_protein, experimental_stage, development_status FROM ProteinExpressionStudies JOIN ProteinExpressionData ON ProteinExpressionStudies.study_id = ProteinExpressionData.study_id JOIN BiopharmaceuticalDevelopment ON ProteinExpressionData.data_id = BiopharmaceuticalDevelopment.data_id WHERE BiopharmaceuticalDevelopment.development_status = 'In Progress' ORDER BY sample_date ASC;

SELECT p.protein_name, r.measurement, s.sample_date FROM Proteins p JOIN Samples s ON p.protein_id = s.protein_id JOIN Results r ON s.sample_id = r.sample_id WHERE r.measurement > 10;

SELECT gene_name, gene_sequence FROM GeneInformation WHERE LENGTH(gene_sequence) > 1000;

SELECT s.sample_name, g.gene_name, c.condition_description FROM StudyResults sr JOIN ProteinSamples s ON sr.sample_id = s.sample_id JOIN GeneInformation g ON sr.gene_id = g.gene_id JOIN ExperimentalConditions c ON sr.condition_id = c.condition_id WHERE sr.result_id = 1;
SELECT p.participant_name, count(*) AS total_results FROM StudyParticipants p JOIN StudyResults sr ON p.participant_id = sr.result_id GROUP BY p.participant_name HAVING total_results > 3;
